<https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_A2_FS_DbPreservation.ttl> a ftr:Metric, dqv:Metric, dcat:Resource ;
    dcterms:identifier "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_A2_FS_DbPreservation.ttl"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_A2_FS_DbPreservation.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcat:landingPage "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_A2_FS_DbPreservation.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcterms:title "FAIR Metric - A2 - Metadata - Database declares preservation policy (registry evaluation)"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "FM_A2_FS_DbPreservation"^^xsd:string ;
    vivo:abbreviation "FM_A2_FS_DbPreservation"^^xsd:string ;
    dcterms:description """**What is being measured?**

This metric evaluates whether the database declares a preservation policy. In FAIRsharing, this corresponds to a non-empty Preservation Policy URL. Expected input is the DOI or URL of the registry (e.g. FAIRsharing) record under evaluation.

**Why should we measure it?**

A2 requires that metadata remain accessible even when the data are no longer available. Information describing a database's preservation commitments helps users and assessment services understand how the database intends to preserve its records over time. The presence of a Preservation Policy URL does not imply that the underlying policy is adequate, implemented or effective. It demonstrates only that preservation information has been provided.

This metric has similarities with **FAIR Metric - A2 - Metadata - Database persistence policy**, which also evaluates declared preservation commitments at the database level. Whereas that metric begins with a research object identifier and uses FAIRsharing as a source of evidence about the hosting database, this metric begins with a registry record identifier as part of an evaluation of the database itself."""^^xsd:string ;
    dcat:keyword "FAIR"^^xsd:string ;
    schema:about "Not applicable"^^xsd:string ;
    ftr:applicationArea <http://www.fairsharing.org/ontology/subject/SRAO_0000401> ;
    ftr:inDimension <https://w3id.org/fair/principles/terms/A2> ;
    dcat:version "1.0.0"^^xsd:string ;
    
    
    ftr:status "Active"@en ;
     
    
    
    
    
